== 9. e4 ==
White strikes in the center, opening up the dark-squared bishop in the process.

Black's main move is '''[[/9...c5/]]''', looking to break up White's center immediately. This move is played in the vast majority of games, and is Black's best option to open up the light-squared bishop and fight for an advantage.

A very rare sideline is '''[[/9...b4/]]''', the Pirc variation. This is the only other move (according to chess engines) that doesn't give White a winning advantage, since it gains a tempo on White's knight. 

